title: MLflow cloned repository is not working when deployed using docker image
body:
### System information

- **OS Platform and Distribution (e.g., Linux Ubuntu 16.04)**: Ubuntu
- **MLflow installed from (source or binary)**: source
- **MLflow version (run ``mlflow --version``)**: 1.28.1.dev0
- **Python version**: 3.7


### Code to reproduce issue

mlflow.create_experiment()
import mlflow.pipelines

### Describe the problem

We found out that new version of MLflow is released which is causing this issue. 
Tags passed while creating an experiment are not getting saved in postgresql db and while running

mlflow --version

Getting below error:

Traceback (most recent call last):
